        "header": "Abstract",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2603.10256/2603.10256v1/x1.png",
                "caption": "Figure 1:Unified Audio-Visual Personalization with ID-LoRA. ID-LoRA takes a reference audio clip and a target first frame as input. Unlike cascaded pipelines that treat modalities separately, ID-LoRA jointly generates synchronized video and audio in a single pass. This unified approach allows a text prompt to simultaneously dictate novel content, such as a specific speaking style and environmental acoustics (e.g., “a jackhammer is drilling in the background”), while ensuring the subject’s vocal identity and visual likeness are preserved across the generated sequence. Video examples with audio\nare available in the supplementary material.",
                "position": 362
            }
        ]
