                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2603.10256/2603.10256v1/x2.png",
                "caption": "Figure 2:ID-LoRA (overview).Target first frame and reference audio are encoded into latents, concatenated with noisy targets, and fed to a shared LTX-2 DiT adapted with In-Context LoRA. Reference audio tokens receivenegativetemporal positions in the RoPE space, cleanly separating them from the target tokens. Joint text conditioning yields synchronized, identity-preserving video and audio whose acoustics follow the prompt and adapted to the new environment.",
